WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:15.188
Signing paperwork used to mean printing, scanning, and chasing people down. In your
portal, it's a click. Let's sign the Bylaws together.

00:15.488 --> 00:22.290
Open Documents... find the Bylaws of Adams Infinite Legacy... and click Open in
DocuSeal.

00:22.590 --> 00:36.736
Welcome to the signing room. Up top, the document itself. Below, the signer list — the
whole board — with a green Signed check for everyone who's done. We're at three of
seven.

00:37.036 --> 00:48.902
When it's your turn, there's a Sign now button next to your name. Click it... and that's
it. Your signature is recorded, dated, and counted — four of seven now.

00:49.202 --> 01:00.396
Need a nudge? Remind sends a gentle email to one person. Or click Email board to sign,
and everyone still pending hears from you at once.

01:00.696 --> 01:11.746
When the last signature lands, the status flips to Fully signed, and the document files
itself in the library. Speaking of tracking — that's our next video.
